Package edu.monash.fit2099.interfaces

Interface GroundInterface

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Crater, Crop, Dirt, Fence, Floor, Floor, Ground, LockedDoor, Tree, Tree, Wall
    public interface GroundInterface
    This interface provides the ability to add methods to Ground, without modifying code in the engine, or downcasting references in the game.

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      java.lang.Boolean canPlant()
      Method that is used to determine whether a Ground Object can be used to plant crops
      void fertilise()
      Method used to fertilise a crop, the ripeTurns will be incremented by 10.
      java.lang.Boolean isFertilised()
      Method that is used to determine whether a Crop can be fertilised
      java.lang.Boolean isRipe()
      Method that is used to determine whether a Crop is ripe

    • Method Detail

      • canPlant

        java.lang.Boolean canPlant()
        Method that is used to determine whether a Ground Object can be used to plant crops
        Returns:
        true if the ground can be used to plant crops and false otherwise

      • isFertilised

        java.lang.Boolean isFertilised()
        Method that is used to determine whether a Crop can be fertilised
        Returns:
        true if the crop can be fertilised and false otherwise, if the Ground Object is not a Crop it will return null.

      • fertilise

        void fertilise()
        Method used to fertilise a crop, the ripeTurns will be incremented by 10.

      • isRipe

        java.lang.Boolean isRipe()
        Method that is used to determine whether a Crop is ripe
        Returns:
        true if the crop is ripe and false otherwise, if the Ground Object is not a Crop it will return null.
